<p>LG dryer door lock replacement costs <strong>$150–220 total</strong> in Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County — one of our lowest-cost repairs. OEM part, door switch test, hinge and alignment check, control board communication verification, and a test cycle confirming the dryer starts and runs. The $65 diagnostic fee is waived when you approve the repair. We see door lock failures regularly on 4–6 year old units in Pasadena and Glendale — the mechanical latch or electronic lock wears before other major components, but the fix is straightforward and inexpensive.</p>
